a good book is hard to find i picked up this o'conner book because every once in awhile i hear about her being `` the definitive voice of the south '' or `` very disturbing '' - i like disturbing and since i 'm not overly familiar with the south , the definitive voice of it seems a good place to start . but i just could n't do it . i read maybe 4 stories before i had to put it down for good . i found the characterizations sophomoric and , well -- i suspect the overt , unsubtle , judgemental observations constantly being offered were snide parody , read in this day of self-consciousness they read like pandering to the lowest common denominator . timely , maybe . timeless , it 's not